values:
Wow. I haven't posted in forever.
There's srsly something wrong. I even spend way less time on my compy. I go for daaays without even turning it on. lol crazy.
I must be getting a real life... or something like that.

So keeping this short; the basics:

I'm still living with my cousin Julia. 
Probably moving out in a week or two.
Might not be able to move into my own place til the beginning of December.
School's fine for now. I just take it one project at a time.
B/c I've been so bust lately I've made no progress at FF VII.
I'm totally enjoying my weekend off... but then I have to go work like Tuesday night. ><
I have to go buy groceries.
I bought dope as boots today from Abbey.
I hung out with Kaly today. That was awesome. I haven't seen her in like, forever!
I so voted on the 7th but I can not believe Brad Wall won. Double Gross. (Who invited Brad Wall? That guy's a cunt.)
I need to start buying christmas gifts but I have like zero point zero zero dollars for that.
I'm gonna go play some Phoenix Wright. <3

P.S. Omg Cloud bought me the first season of X-Files!! <3 I am so watching it tomorrow night. ^^

YA I LIKE SLACKING!
(I don't know why but I've had that pancake song in my head for like hours.)

Anyways. I haven't died or anything.
I am so attending college now.
My schedule is awesome.

Monday, Wednesday and Friday: 
11:30 - 12:20 Archeology and biological anthropology 112
12:30 -   1:20 Political Science 112
then
Tuesday and Thursday: 
11:30 - 12:50 Introduction to Philosophy 110
  1:00 -   2:20 Composition and Literature 110

Yeah. Good times. <3
 I so wanna go see DJ Champion too! I think he'll be at Louis on the 25th. I still hafta check the age limit on that show.

I'm kinda poor right now though. Thanks a lot stupidly expensive text books. 
I think I'm getting paid this weekend. I hope at least.
Oh and for anyone who didn't know. I moved out. I'm living with my cousin Julia in an attic suite, but I don't know how long this will last.

I think we're going out for coffee in a lil bit.
We won't be out too long. I have a lot of reading to do tonight.

I can't describe how much I MOTHERFUCKIN' <3 TRANFORMERS!!!

Oh, Bumble-Bee. <3 Oh Jazz. <3 Oh Optimus Prime! <3

So,
 I don't really recall the last time I wrote a real LJ post... here goes.
Just got back from Emerald lake... really good times. I'm glad I went. I wasn't really sure how much fun I'd have without Sadie and Lindsay but it rocked. Becky has a cabin at the same lake so she, Chantal, Chantal's Boyfriend Dave, Shanda, Mitch, Shayla, Janelle Hollabitz ,Brianne George and Kelsi Allen were already up there. We spent the night before Canada day partying in Becky's cabin and it was super fun.
Anyways I only got a little bit of a burn, b/c I applied like way too much sunscreen (two coats) very often. Yay! The lake was really nice, we went kayaking and we played Super Mario Bros. 3 when it rained. ^^ I think we'll all have to go up sometime in August.
Moving on.
 
OMG, I am so pumped to go see Tranformers tonight, Sorry Cloud we just have to go without you. 
Maybe you can talk Alyssa into taking you.
Lindsay calls me up yesterday and was like "umm, where is everyone?" I explained that Brayden, Hunter and I just got back from the lake and that Sadie's in Calgary. Then she's like oh well ok ... we NEED to go see Trasformers! and I was like ho-m-g I completely forgot about it since I was in the bush for like 4 days.
We call Brayden and head over to the theatre (also with us was Lindsays friend Cory, a pretty cool guy) we get there at like 8 planning to go to the 10 o' clock show but... turns out ALL the shows that night are sold out. Ok, we buy tickets for tonight at 10! Awesome!

We had a good time last night anyways. We were all feeling a little poor though. So we did a lot to keep it under budget. 
Renting movies?
 too much. So we stopped by my place considering we've got plenty. 
Going to DQ? 
no way, not unless we planned to dine and dash. Lindsay volunteers the half box of vanilla in her fridge and we go to super store for toppings and drinks.
We roll up at super store and all put 5 bux up on the table. We get an extra box of ice cream (super obscure brand) and scout out that sweet chocolate hard shell stuff, but it had to be twix brand since thats all they had. Drinks! We buy 3 bottles of PC fruit pop and a no name apple juice. Finally we dish out for a 5 dollar no name frozen pizza! yay we had 2 bux to spare for gas.
Oh and we couldn't be bothered with bags so we walked out of the store looking a lil weird. It was awesome.


I read all my transformers comics (aka 2) today, I so can't wait.
Brayden sucks at planning though. He's been out all day and finally I found out he's at cheerleading camp til 9. Shit. The lady at the theatre told us she'd been telling everyone to show up an hour early for seats. We were gonna go at 8. So yay, Cory can drive buuuuut he doesn't have a car. Lindsay does and her dad (who's out working) has the only key to it. She said he didn't know if he'd be home by 8... so I'm waitin around to see.
Tick Tock.
This entries a cliffhangar.
So hopefully Cory and Lindsay pull up to my door so we can have a sweet party tonight... and maybe I'll come home and write a 1 line review.

Oh... who's cool?  I'm cool.

B'Okay T'Shane.

So I haven't updated in a while... but I've been busy.
Ok. Oh-so many days ago, like on the 6th Easter break was upon us.
Erica and I went to Edmonton the night of the 9th, arriving at like 5:30 in the morning and stayed at Michaels.
We slept most of that morning and then went downtown and to the Shaw Conference Centre!
We went to see the Silver Sun Pickups and OK Go! <333
XD oh I guess they were both "opening" for Snow Patrol.... but I don't really care for them and neither does Erica.
We would have had to be at like the back of the line but we rock and randomly snuck in some back doors. 
So we were at the very front!
The SSP were really awesome!
There was a screen set up behind the band and randomly during "Little Lovers So Polite" Tim Nordwind was backstage and they projected him onto the screen. He was wearing a jumpsuit and well Erica filmed it.
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zp-jq072v2M You can watch it here. I won't spoil it too much but lemme say it's amazing and it involves lettuce.
Me and Tim Nordwind made like SO much eye contact and OK Go did the Million Ways Dance!
We had brought some sweet Saskatchewan postcards and write really weird shit on the backs of them/
Afterwards we hung around outside for like 2 hours til finally we were like the only ones there and and Tim and Andy came out and signed some shit for us. <333
Tim said Damian would probably be coming out soon but we waited around for another hour til like the crew left without sign 
of Damian OR Dan...
sigh. We'll have to actually mail them their postcards. those lamers.
So anyways we had such a great time, even though everyone in Edmonton is like super rude.

We came back on the 11th. I so have confidence in my ability to navigate big cities. This totally confirmed my skills. We took the buses and LRT everywhere and totally didn't get lost.
We rock.

Oh then later that week on friday the 13th Michelle picked Lindsay and up and we met up with Annie, Sonya and Brittany at the foodcourt in Midtown. We ate, walked around and then went to go see The Hush Sound, Boys Like Girls and HelloGoodbye. The Hush Sound is an amazing band and their merch guy is too cool. His moustache was so sweet. We all bought Hush Sound t-shirts too even though they weren't the headliners. XD I guess their shirts were the coolest.
The Odeon was like teh packed. Erica was there and I saw Cordell too. I didn't like Boys Like Girls too much..they just seemed a bit bland but Lindsay insisted they were hot so ok. HelloGoodbye were really cool even though they didn't play "I Saw It On Your Keyboard". It was super fun.
Oh after that we all went to Mac's for frosters and then bowling with like 12 other kids at like 1 in the morning. Good Times.
I haven't really done a lot of schoolwork lately... but I did read a lot of FountainHead today. 

Oh Sadie and I saw Meet the Robinsons on Monday I think.
It was way sweeter than I expected. The characters were so super cool! XD I even aspire to be likw Wilbur now.
Anyways yeah... I tried keeping this short. I'm pretty much done now. 
We still have a lot of work to do on our OtaFest Cosplay... Maybe we'll do accessories tomorrow. Hopefully we'll get something done!

B'Okay, T'Shane! 

This has been such a dope weekend. Busy and FUN! ^^ 
I guess it all started friday at lunch. I ate some food and then ditched school to go get my hair cut. It was fun, I always love getting my hair done. ^^ At first I was kinda worried b/c Johnny like made it all pouffy and curly and it kinda looked like I was from the 80's but I actually really like it now. I think it's cute as long as I style it properly. Friday night I showered and then fell asleep on it and it looked soooo dumb when I got up. XD 
Anyways I then went back to school to pick up my stuff. I spent some time lying on the floor with Brayden and Lindsay and then hooked up with my Cousin Julia and her Boyfriend Logan. Earlier she had told me she wanted to go shopping but then when she picked me up she was like oh...we already did that let's go out for supper! That was fine but then she wanted to go hang out at our Aunt Lorna's. We sat there for like ever! I was there so long that I didn't get to go see Blades of Glory with everyone. Oh well, so then Julia had to go, I asked her to drop me off at home but then I was like no the mall, I wanna shop...but then I was like no... I should go home and see mom. I got home,l and my mom wasn't there... she had gone to the mall. So was like eff this, I'm going shopping. So I put on some cute jewelery and packed up my pokemon backpack nice. Once I got there I just wandered around. I saw Dalena and talked to her for a bit. Then at like 20 to 9 I saw Chelsie at A&W and I talked to her for like 15 minutes til Shannon showed up. XD She told me about a pretty weird dream she had. Shannon told me about how she and Sarah were gonna try getting into the Juno show at The Odeon and hook up with the cool C.D. Plus kids inside. I really wanted to go but totally hadn't even thought about it b/c it was a 19+ show and security around the Odeon is tight. She was like come party with us it'll be fun. Then I was like "why not? there's no harm in trying." Then Cy showed up and said he'd meet us there later too. I hung out with Shannon til Sarah was done work and then we headed over. 
So exciting. We stood in the wrong line for awhile... smooth. Finally we got to the ticket lady and we didn't even get carded!! Eee. ^^  
That show was SO dope. Like amazing line up. First up, 'You Say Party! We say Die!', I'd never heard them before but they were really cool. Some experimental techno rock. Really fun. Then 'Shout Out Out Out Out'. OMG that was fun. I really love their music and the crowd was so into it. ^^ Everybody was jumping (including me). I think it was Connie who spilled beer all over Sarah and I. Then some guys were trying to crowd surf and one of them totally fell on my head. XD it was cool I didn't fall and I totally recovered with ease. Next up 'Malajube'. WOOT! I <3 these guys so awesome. So we went up to the front of the stage to check em out. ^^ It was amazing watching them live. 
We wanted some merch after that so we went to the coat check to get our bags but Shannon had to leave. I think I got the last Malajube t-shirt. XD it's a medium and white but... it;s cool. I also got a c.d. and some buttons. <333 
Sarah was all tired out from Malajube I guess, she kinda wanted to leave but Devon offered to drive us home after they went on. I was really impressed by D.J. Champion. There were 7 people on stage. The DJ and the band with him called the 'G-Strings' which consisted of a singer, a bassist and 4 guitarists. Super awesome and their music was really varied. 
I was just so impressed that we got in. ^^ Then nobody even questioned us. The dude at the bar even tried to sell us some kokanees, but at 7 bux a drink? no thanks.  
I was like Fuck going to the Junos ceremony, I was just at THE best show of the weekend! <3 
I still have a couple bruises from the pit but most of them are faded so I figure they'll basically be gone by tomorrow. 
I didn't get home til like quarter after 3. My feet were pretty sore, seeing as I was clever and decided walking everywhere that day was a good idea and had been jumping around for like 5 hours. I took a shower and went to bed at 4:30. 

DUN DUN ( The Law and Order version) 
9:34 AM. Saturday. 
My mom wakes me up.  
I was dazed for like a minute but then she asked me how the show was and I got all excited telling her about it til finally she was like, "Enough!". 
XD So it was fine getting up so early. We borrowed my Uncle John's macked out truck for the day so my mom and I went shopping. I bought some cool new jeans, a dress, a polo shirt, a striped t-shirt oh and white capris. XD maybe I was really tired but I was like ahahaha I should try on some white pants. Then I was like ooh these are cute and actually bought them. They won't stay clean for long... 
Oh I also bought a cute 40's style skirt and SUCH a cute polka dot tank top which fits me so awesomely. ^^ I don't really know where I'll wear them but they are really cute. 
We took Lachlan to some kids birthday party, went out for lunch, went grocery shopping, picked Lachlan up and then chilled at home for a bit. I was really tired so I went to sleep at like 1 in the morning and then slept for like 12 hours. yay. ^^ 
I woke up and watched House of Flying Daggers. <3 Half martial arts, half make out session. 
Then I took like the longest bath, ever. 
I watched Juno coverage with my mom but they were really lame. too much Nelly Furtado. Her music actually sucks... not even trying to be mean, it's just... sucky.  
Also... how come the Hip didn't win some shit? wtf. I did enjoy Gordon Downies poem and DJ Champion rocked out too. 
Oh well. Now I'm eating scrumptious Chinese food that I got from some cutie delivery boy. ^^ 
Fried Rice rocks hardcore! 

Longest LJ entry, ever.

H'okay SO!

Tomorrow, going on das trip to Edmonton, not returning til late Friday evening. ^^
Cool, right? 
Yes.
 Also I'm sooo excited right now, b/c
senydegger
 just made me suuuch a cute icon involving Reno as a band geek. <3

Ahaha yes. 
I should've tried working on my chemistry lab but truth is I have such little clue as to how to do it...T_T.
I'll figure it out tomorrow morning maybe?
Oh well. I'm tired. I should go to bed but for some odd reason I fee pretty awake.
Even though during the last two nights I've only like 6 hours of sleep.
Hum Dee Dum... We had that concert tonight to show off our skills before we go but XD gawd that FreeRide.
I'm pretty sure we like played that repeat like 3 times at least but I'm proud that we kept going though and made it kind of sound ok.
^^ Brayden drove me home AND bought me an Icecap. He roxors.
